	<element name="Throwing Needle" type="Weapon" source="Homebrew" id="ID_BREW_WEAPON_THROWING_NEEDLE">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FINESSE, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_THROWN</supports>
		<description>
			<p>The Throwing Needle is a weapon of finesse and precision. It takes much training to throw one accurately enough. When used, these are more often used for targeting pressure points and nonlethal practice. When a hit is achieved, the user can force the target to make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become stunned for 1 round. Due to the nature of the physical shock the body goes through, and the accuracy required, the user can only do this once per encounter per target.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="cp">5</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.25">1/4 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">40/80</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d6</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY_DART</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
